        <h2>About Us</h2>
        <p>
        The Choir of Students of the Bandung Institute of Technology, commonly known as PASUMA STT Bandung, is a Student Activity Unit under the auspices of the Student Executive Board of the Bandung Institute of Technology, based at the Bandung Institute of Technology. PASUMA is one of the Student Activity Units engaged in the field of Arts, specifically in the realm of vocal music.<br><br>
        PASUMA has been in existence since 2012 and was officially inaugurated by the Bandung Institute of Technology on November 17, 2015. The establishment of PASUMA aims to provide a means and infrastructure for developing and channeling the talents of students at the Bandung Institute of Technology, particularly in the field of choral singing. <br><br> 
        PASUMA has monthly routine activities such as rehearsals and annual routine events like the Bandung Institute of Technology graduation, Friendship Night, and the Choir's Anniversary, as well as participating in competitions outside the campus. <br> <br>
        PASUMA also has a work program called the Singing Competition, a singing competition that has been held for the past 2 years. In the second year of the Singing Competition, PASUMA collaborated with the Ministry of SBDO STT Bandung and the Music Society Student Activity Unit of STT Bandung in the STTB Got Talent event.
        </p>
